Primary HIV infection is usually a nonspecific illness with fever , headache , myalgia , fatigue , and a sore throat . Generalized lymphadenopathy and a maculopapular rash may occur . Following primary infection there is a prolonged asymptomatic period before the appearance of the clinical manifestations of a loss of immune control over infectious pathogens and cancers . Common presenting AIDS defining illnesses are tuberculosis , atypical mycobacterial infections , recurrent bacterial infections , Pneumocystis jirovecii pneumonia , candidiasis , Kaposi sarcoma , lymphoma , cryptococcal meningitis , and CMV disease .
