Infective sporozoites are inoculated by bite from anopheles mosquitoes and through the bloodstream and lymphatics reach the liver where they differentiate into tissue schizonts that release merozoites , or to a dormant stage -LRB- hypnozoite -RRB- that can become active after months or years , causing relapse . Merozoites released from liver mostly infect reticulocytes that develop to schizonts , rupture and release merozoites that will infect new reticulocytes -LRB- this cycle takes 48 hours -RRB- . Gametocytes are able to infect mosquitoes during a blood meal .
