vCJD is characterized by a relatively early age of onset -LRB- 28 years -RRB- and prominent early psychiatric symptoms : anxiety , depression , agitation , delusions , and unpleasant sensory symptoms . Neurological features are : unsteadiness , difficulty walking , and involuntary movements . Memory loss progresses to severe cognitive impairment and , at the time of death , patients have become unable to move or speak . The median duration of illness is 14 months .
