HCV infection has a worldwide prevalence of 2 % and an estimated 130 to 170 million chronic cases globally . The highest prevalences are found in Africa and Asia . Egypt has the highest HCV prevalence rate -LRB- 22 % -RRB- , likely due to a national schistosomiasis treatment campaign since the 1960s that re-used needles . In developing countries the high prevalence is likely due to poor infection control practices in the healthcare system -LRB- therapeutic injections , blood transfusion , surgery -RRB- . Also local practices in the community , like acupuncture and cutting of the skin with unsterile knives , are other important routes of transmission . In Asia it is common to receive injections for various illnesses outside the hospital setting . In developed countries HCV is mainly transmitted by IVDU , accounting for 70 -- 80 % of HCV infections .
