Crustaceans infected with metacercaria larvae are ingested by the reservoir host , excyst in the gut and migrate to the tissues , usually the lungs . There they encapsulate , mature , and lay eggs . Eggs enter the sputum which is coughed up and swallowed , then pass out in the feces into water and hatch in 2 -- 4 weeks into miracidia larvae . These penetrate the body of the vector snail , where they develop in about 2 months into cercaria larvae which enter and encyst in freshwater crabs and crayfish .
Infective sporozoites are inoculated by the bite of anopheles mosquitoes and through the bloodstream and lymphatics reach the liver where they differentiate into tissue schizonts that release merozoites , or to a dormant stage -LRB- hypnozoite -RRB- that can become active after months or years , causing relapse . Merozoites released from liver infect erythrocytes that develop to schizonts , rupture and release merozoites that will infect new erythrocytes -LRB- this cycle takes 48 hours -RRB- . Some merozoites develop into gametocytes that are able to infect mosquitoes during a blood meal .
By flea bite for the bubonic form , by the respiratory route for the pneumonic form ; handling carcasses or eating meat of infected animals . Person-to-person transmission occurs through the bite of fleas -LRB- bubonic form -RRB- or respiratory droplets -LRB- pneumonic form -RRB- .
No specific treatment is available .
There is an asexual phase in humans and a sexual phase in the vector mosquito . The mosquito injects sporozoites that invade human liver cells where they reproduce and develop to merozoites , which , after release , infect erythrocytes . The erythrocytic stages multiply around 10-fold every 48-hours . Erythrocytes can release gametocytes which infect mosquitoes during a blood meal . In the mosquito , gametocytes develop into sporozoites .
Typically a cardiopulmonary infection as opposed to the primarily renal infection produced by Old World hantaviruses ; renal involvement and hemorrhage are rare in NewWorld cases . Symptoms are fever , myalgia , and GI pain , followed by sudden onset of respiratory distress and hypotension , with rapid progression to respiratory failure and shock . Convalescence is prolonged . CFR is 35 -- 60 % .
The fungus grows as a mycelium in the environment and in human or animal tissue it converts into a budding yeast .
Supportive ; vitamin A supplementation is important to avoid the complications of vitamin A deficiency resulting from the infection . Efficacy of ribavirin is unproven .
