The global dengue distribution follows vector presence and introduction of the virus , and occurs basically between the 10 C isotherms . Autochthonous dengue fever cases appeared in Europe for the first time in 2010 , north of 10 C isotherm and likely transmitted by Ae . albopictus -LRB- see Aedes agypti and Aedes albopictus map -RRB- . There is strong seasonality , correlated with the rainy season , which produces a marked increase in vectors because more mosquito-breeding sites become available then . Two , 3 or all 4 serotypes may occur concurrently . DHF/DSS in many countries is most often seen in children suffering a secondary infection with a different serotype . Incidence rates of up to 3 % have been seen in dengue na√µve populations such as are found in some Pacific islands .
Human infections occur via two main transmission routes : -LRB- 1 -RRB- mosquito bite , and -LRB- 2 -RRB- direct or indirect contact with the blood or organs of infected animals -LRB- e.g. slaughtering , butchering , veterinary procedures , animal births , disposing of carcasses or fetuses -RRB- by percutaneous inoculation or inhaling aerosols . Transmissionmay be possible via consumption of raw milk of an infected animal . Person-toperson transmission has not been described . However , humans develop high viral loads in the blood , and may transmit virus to contacts .
