Katayama syndrome is an acute form of schistosomiasis , caused by the host immune response to developing larvae and early egg production and presents with nocturnal fever , cough , myalgia , headache , and abdominal pain . Katayama syndrome is more common among infected nonimmune individuals -LRB- e.g. travelers -RRB- and relatively rare among local residentswith exposure since childhood . S. japonicum causes intestinal schistosomiasis with : diarrhea , abdominal pain , blood in the stool , hepatosplenomegaly . Chronic infection leads to liver fibrosis and portal hypertension , anemia , and altered growth and cognitive development in infected children ; seizures due to egg granulomas in brain or spinal cord . Infection does not produce full immunity , so reinfection occurs . S.mekongi causes similar , but milder , disease compared to S. japonicum .
